[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cancer centre costing £10m planned for Northallerton hospital

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Plans have been unveiled for a £10m cancer treatment centre at a North Yorkshire hospital.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The facility would be located at the Friarage Hospital in Northallerton.
It is being built by the Macmillan charity and is part funded with a donation from local businessman Sir Robert Ogden.
If planning permission is granted, building work on the new centre could begin this summer, with the project due to be completed by 2018.
