The building would house a chemotherapy treatment lounge to treat up to 35 patients a day, treatment and consulting rooms and therapy facilities.
Paul McCavana, Macmillan head of services for the North, said: "This is a fantastic opportunity to provide a state-of-the art cancer care facility, all under one roof, for people in and around Northallerton.
"It will provide a space for patients to have all their needs assessed, not just physical and clinical, but their financial, emotional and psychological needs too."
